	<h1>Quadratic Equations</h1>
	
	<h2>Discriminant</h2>
	<div>
		<p>
			In the quadratic formula, the expression underneath the square root sign is called the <em>discriminant</em>
			of the quadratic equation, and is often represented using an upper case <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mi>D</mi></math> or <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>&#x394;</mi></math>.
		</p>
		<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
			<mrow>
				<mi>&#x394;</mi>
				<mo>=</mo>
				<msup>
              		<mi>b</mi>
              		<mn>2</mn>
            	</msup>
            	<mo>-</mo>
            	<mrow>
	              <mn>4</mn>
	              <mo>&#x2062;</mo>
	              <mi>a</mi>
	              <mo>&#x2062;</mo>
	              <mi>c</mi>
            	</mrow>
			</mrow>
		</math>
	</div>
</rubricBlock>
